328  private void CheckCharacterPickup()
329  {
330  if (MyPerGameSettings.Game != GameEnum.ME_GAME) return;
331 
332  // Add characters that we have in the game and that we know are not picking stuff
333  HashSet<MyDefinitionId> ignoredCharacters = new HashSet<MyDefinitionId>();
334  ignoredCharacters.Add(new MyDefinitionId(typeof(MyObjectBuilder_Character), "Peasant_male"));
335  ignoredCharacters.Add(new MyDefinitionId(typeof(MyObjectBuilder_Character), "Medieval_barbarian"));
336  ignoredCharacters.Add(new MyDefinitionId(typeof(MyObjectBuilder_Character), "Medieval_deer"));
337  ignoredCharacters.Add(new MyDefinitionId(typeof(MyObjectBuilder_Character), "Medieval_wolf"));
338 
339  MyContainerDefinition containerDef = null;
340  string error = "Character definition {0} is missing a pickup component! " +
341  "You will not be able to pickup things with this character! " +
342  "See the player character in EntityContainers.sbc and EntityComponents.sbc for an example.";
343 
344  foreach (var pair in m_definitions.m_characters)
345  {
346  var characterDef = pair.Value;
347  if (ignoredCharacters.Contains(characterDef.Id)) continue;
348 
349  bool hasContainerDef = TryGetContainerDefinition(characterDef.Id, out containerDef);
350 
351  if (!hasContainerDef)
352  {
353  MyDefinitionErrors.Add(MyModContext.UnknownContext, String.Format(error, characterDef.Id.ToString()), TErrorSeverity.Warning);
354  continue;
355  }
356 
357  bool foundPickup = false;
358  foreach (var component in containerDef.DefaultComponents)
359  {
360  Type componentType = (Type)component.BuilderType;
361  if (typeof(MyObjectBuilder_CharacterPickupComponent).IsAssignableFrom(componentType))
362  {
363  foundPickup = true;
364  break;
365  }
366  }
367 
368  if (!foundPickup)
369  {
370  MyDefinitionErrors.Add(MyModContext.UnknownContext, String.Format(error, characterDef.Id.ToString()), TErrorSeverity.Warning);
371  }
372  }
373  }

451  private List<Tuple<MyObjectBuilder_Definitions, string>> m_preloadedDefinitionBuilders = null;
452  private List<Tuple<MyObjectBuilder_Definitions, string>> GetDefinitionBuilders(MyModContext context, HashSet<string> preloadSet = null)
453  {
454 
455  // Reload definitions from cache on official release
456  if (m_preloadedDefinitionBuilders != null && context == MyModContext.BaseGame && preloadSet == null)
457  return m_preloadedDefinitionBuilders;
458 
459  var definitionBuilders = new List<Tuple<MyObjectBuilder_Definitions, string>>(30);
460  foreach (var file in MyFileSystem.GetFiles(context.ModPathData, "*.sbc", VRage.FileSystem.MySearchOption.AllDirectories))
461  {
462  if (preloadSet != null && !preloadSet.Contains(Path.GetFileName(file))) continue;
463 
464  if (Path.GetFileName(file) == "DefinitionsToPreload.sbc") continue;
465  context.CurrentFile = file;
466 
467  ProfilerShort.Begin("Verify Integrity");
468  MyDataIntegrityChecker.HashInFile(file);
469  MyObjectBuilder_Definitions builder = null;
470 
471  ProfilerShort.BeginNextBlock("Try Parse as Prefab");
472  try
473  {
474  builder = CheckPrefabs(file);
475  }
476  catch (Exception e)
477  {
478  FailModLoading(context, innerException: e);
479  return null;
480  }
481 
482  ProfilerShort.BeginNextBlock("Parse");
483  if (builder == null)
484  {
485  builder = Load<MyObjectBuilder_Definitions>(file);
486  }
487 
488  if (builder == null)
489  {
490  FailModLoading(context);
491  return null;
492  }
493 
494  definitionBuilders.Add(new Tuple<MyObjectBuilder_Definitions, string>(builder, file));
495  ProfilerShort.End();
496  }
497 
498  if (context == MyModContext.BaseGame && preloadSet == null && MyFakes.ENABLE_PRELOAD_DEFINITIONS)
499  m_preloadedDefinitionBuilders = definitionBuilders;
500 
501  return definitionBuilders;
502  }

504  private void LoadDefinitions(MyModContext context, DefinitionSet definitionSet, bool failOnDebug = true, bool isPreload = false)
505  {
506  HashSet<string> preloadSet = null;
507 
508  if (isPreload)
509  {
510  preloadSet = GetPreloadSet();
511  if (preloadSet == null) return;
512  }
513 
514  if (!MyFileSystem.DirectoryExists(context.ModPathData))
515  return;
516 
517  m_currentLoadingSet = definitionSet;
518  definitionSet.Context = context;
519  m_transparentMaterialsInitialized = false;
520 
521  ProfilerShort.Begin("Load definitions from files");
522  var definitionsBuilders = GetDefinitionBuilders(context, preloadSet);
523  if (definitionsBuilders == null)
524  return;
525 
526  ProfilerShort.BeginNextBlock("Postprocessing");
527 
528  var phases = new Action<MyObjectBuilder_Definitions, MyModContext, DefinitionSet, bool>[]
529  {
530  LoadPhase1,
531  LoadPhase2,
532  LoadPhase3,
533  LoadPhase4,
534  LoadPhase5,
535  };
536 
537  for (int i = 0; i < phases.Length; i++)
538  {
539  try
540  {
541  ProfilerShort.Begin("Phase " + (i + 1));
542  foreach (var builder in definitionsBuilders)
543  {
544  context.CurrentFile = builder.Item2;
545  var phase = phases[i];
546  phase(builder.Item1, context, definitionSet, failOnDebug);
547  }
548  ProfilerShort.End();
549  }
550  catch (Exception e)
551  {
552  FailModLoading(context, phase: i, phaseNum: phases.Length, innerException: e);
553  ProfilerShort.End();
554  ProfilerShort.End();
555  return;
556  }
557  MergeDefinitions();
558  }
559 
560 
561  AfterLoad(context, definitionSet);
562 
563  ProfilerShort.End();
564  }

635  private static void FailModLoading(MyModContext context, int phase = -1, int phaseNum = 0, Exception innerException = null)
636  {
637  string errorMessage = (innerException != null ? ", Following Error occured:" + MyEnvironment.NewLine + innerException.Message + MyEnvironment.NewLine + innerException.Source + MyEnvironment.NewLine + innerException.StackTrace : "");
638  if (phase == -1)
639  MyDefinitionErrors.Add(context, "MOD SKIPPED, Cannot load definition file" + errorMessage, TErrorSeverity.Critical);
640  else
641  MyDefinitionErrors.Add(context, String.Format("MOD PARTIALLY SKIPPED, LOADED ONLY {0}/{1} PHASES" + errorMessage, phase + 1, phaseNum), TErrorSeverity.Critical);
642 
643  if (context.IsBaseGame)
644  {
645  // When original definition fails to load, return to main menu
646  throw new MyLoadingException(String.Format(MyTexts.GetString(MySpaceTexts.LoadingError_ModifiedOriginalContent), context.CurrentFile), innerException);
647  }
648  else
649  {
650  // When definition from MOD fails to load, skip mod loading
651  return;
652  }
653  }

655  private static MyObjectBuilder_Definitions CheckPrefabs(string file)
656  {
657  List<MyObjectBuilder_PrefabDefinition> prefabs = null;
658  using (var fileStream = MyFileSystem.OpenRead(file))
659  {
660  if (fileStream != null)
661  {
662  using (var readStream = fileStream.UnwrapGZip())
663  {
664  if (readStream != null)
665  {
666  CheckXmlForPrefabs(file, ref prefabs, readStream);
667  }
668  }
669  }
670  }
671 
672  MyObjectBuilder_Definitions definitions = null;
673  if (prefabs != null)

675  definitions = new MyObjectBuilder_Definitions();
676  definitions.Prefabs = prefabs.ToArray();
677  }
678  return definitions;

681  private static void CheckXmlForPrefabs(string file, ref List<MyObjectBuilder_PrefabDefinition> prefabs, Stream readStream)
682  {
683  using (XmlReader reader = XmlReader.Create(readStream))
684  {
685  while (reader.Read())
686  {
687  if (reader.IsStartElement())
688  {
689  if (reader.Name == "SpawnGroups")
690  {
691  break;
692  }
693  else if (reader.Name == "Prefabs")
694  {
695  prefabs = new List<MyObjectBuilder_PrefabDefinition>();
696  while (reader.ReadToFollowing("Prefab"))
697  {
698  ReadPrefabHeader(file, ref prefabs, reader);
699  }
700  break;
701  }
702  }
703  }
704  }
705  }

707  private static void ReadPrefabHeader(string file, ref List<MyObjectBuilder_PrefabDefinition> prefabs, XmlReader reader)
708  {
709  MyObjectBuilder_PrefabDefinition definition = new MyObjectBuilder_PrefabDefinition();
710  definition.PrefabPath = file;
711  bool found = reader.ReadToFollowing("Id");
712  Debug.Assert(found);
713 
714  bool useAttrs = false;
715 
716  if (reader.AttributeCount >= 2)
717  {
718  for (int i = 0; i < reader.AttributeCount; ++i)
719  {
720  reader.MoveToAttribute(i);
721 
722  switch (reader.Name)
723  {
724  case "Type":
725  definition.Id.TypeIdString = reader.Value;
726  useAttrs = true;
727  break;
728  case "Subtype":
729  definition.Id.SubtypeId = reader.Value;
730  break;
731  }
732  }
733  }
734 
735  if (!useAttrs)
736  while (reader.Read())
737  {
738  if (reader.IsStartElement())
739  {
740  switch (reader.Name)
741  {
742  case "TypeId":
743  reader.Read();
744  definition.Id.TypeIdString = reader.Value;
745  break;
746  case "SubtypeId":
747  reader.Read();
748  definition.Id.SubtypeId = reader.Value;
749  break;
750  }
751  }
752  else if (reader.NodeType == XmlNodeType.EndElement && reader.Name == "Id")
753  {
754  break;
755  }
756  }
757 
758  prefabs.Add(definition);
759  }

1269  private void LoadScenarios(MyModContext context, DefinitionSet definitionSet, bool failOnDebug = true)
1270  {
1271  var file = Path.Combine(context.ModPathData, "Scenarios.sbx");
1272  if (!MyFileSystem.FileExists(file))
1273  return;
1274 
1275  MyDataIntegrityChecker.HashInFile(file);
1276  var objBuilder = Load<MyObjectBuilder_ScenarioDefinitions>(file);
1277  if (objBuilder == null)
1278  {
1279  MyDefinitionErrors.Add(context, "Scenarios: Cannot load definition file, see log for details", TErrorSeverity.Error);
1280  return;
1281  }
1282 
1283  if (objBuilder.Scenarios != null)
1284  {
1285  MySandboxGame.Log.WriteLine("Loading scenarios");
1286  InitScenarioDefinitions(context, definitionSet.m_definitionsById, definitionSet.m_scenarioDefinitions, objBuilder.Scenarios, failOnDebug);
1287  }
1288 
1289  MergeDefinitions();
1290  }

1292  private void LoadPostProcess()
1293  {
1294  ProfilerShort.Begin("InitVoxelMaterials");
1295  InitVoxelMaterials();
1296  if (m_transparentMaterialsInitialized == false)
1297  {
1298  ProfilerShort.BeginNextBlock("CreateTransparentMaterials");
1299  CreateTransparentMaterials();
1300  m_transparentMaterialsInitialized = true;
1301  }
1302  ProfilerShort.BeginNextBlock("InitRopeDefinitions");
1303  InitRopeDefinitions();
1304  ProfilerShort.BeginNextBlock("InitBlockGroups");
1305  InitBlockGroups();
1306  ProfilerShort.BeginNextBlock("PostprocessComponentGroups");
1307  PostprocessComponentGroups();
1308  ProfilerShort.BeginNextBlock("PostprocessComponentBlocks");
1309  PostprocessComponentBlocks();

1361  private void InitMultiBlockDefinitions()
1362  {
1363  if (MyFakes.ENABLE_MULTIBLOCKS)
1364  {
1365  // Initialize min, max values for blocks in multiblocks
1366  var multiBlockDefinitions = GetMultiBlockDefinitions();
1367  foreach (var multiBlockDef in multiBlockDefinitions)
1368  {
1369  multiBlockDef.Min = Vector3I.MaxValue;
1370  multiBlockDef.Max = Vector3I.MinValue;
1371 
1372  foreach (var partDef in multiBlockDef.BlockDefinitions)
1373  {
1374  MyCubeBlockDefinition blockDefinition;
1375  if (MyDefinitionManager.Static.TryGetCubeBlockDefinition(partDef.Id, out blockDefinition) && blockDefinition != null)
1376  {
1377  MatrixI blockRotation = new MatrixI(partDef.Forward, partDef.Up);
1378  Vector3I sizeRotated = Vector3I.Abs(Vector3I.TransformNormal(blockDefinition.Size - Vector3I.One, ref blockRotation));
1379  partDef.Max = partDef.Min + sizeRotated;
1380 
1381  multiBlockDef.Min = Vector3I.Min(multiBlockDef.Min, partDef.Min);
1382  multiBlockDef.Max = Vector3I.Max(multiBlockDef.Max, partDef.Max);
1383  }
1384  }
1385 
1386  Debug.Assert(multiBlockDef.Min != Vector3I.MaxValue);
1387  }
1388  }
1389  }

1542  private void PostprocessBlueprints()
1543  {
1544  CachingList<MyBlueprintDefinitionBase> blueprintsToPostprocess = new CachingList<MyBlueprintDefinitionBase>();
1545 
1546  // Cyclically postprocess all blueprints over and over as long as the list changes.
1547  // This is because the blueprint postprocess could depend on other blueprint being postprocessed.
1548  foreach (var entry in m_definitions.m_blueprintsById)
1549  {
1550  var blueprint = entry.Value;
1551  if (blueprint.PostprocessNeeded) blueprintsToPostprocess.Add(blueprint);
1552  }
1553  blueprintsToPostprocess.ApplyAdditions();
1554 
1555  int prevCount = -1;
1556  while (blueprintsToPostprocess.Count != 0 && blueprintsToPostprocess.Count != prevCount)
1557  {
1558  prevCount = blueprintsToPostprocess.Count;
1559  foreach (var blueprint in blueprintsToPostprocess)
1560  {
1561  if (blueprint is MyCompositeBlueprintDefinition) { }
1562  blueprint.Postprocess();
1563  if (!blueprint.PostprocessNeeded) blueprintsToPostprocess.Remove(blueprint);
1564  }
1565  blueprintsToPostprocess.ApplyRemovals();
1566  }
1567 
1568  if (blueprintsToPostprocess.Count != 0)
1569  {
1570  StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("Following blueprints could not be post-processed: ");
1571  foreach (var blueprint in blueprintsToPostprocess)
1572  {
1573  sb.Append(blueprint.Id.ToString());
1574  sb.Append(", ");
1575  }
1576  MyDefinitionErrors.Add(MyModContext.BaseGame, sb.ToString(), TErrorSeverity.Error);
1577  }
1578  }

1580  private void AddEntriesToBlueprintClasses()
1581  {

1583  {
1584  if (!entry.Enabled) continue;
1585 
1586  MyBlueprintClassDefinition blueprintClass = null;
1587  MyBlueprintDefinitionBase blueprint = null;
1588 
1589  MyDefinitionId classId = new MyDefinitionId(typeof(MyObjectBuilder_BlueprintClassDefinition), entry.Class);
1590  m_definitions.m_blueprintClasses.TryGetValue(classId, out blueprintClass);
1591 
1592  blueprint = FindBlueprintByClassEntry(entry);
1593 
1594  // Block blueprint can be null if the corresponding block is not public.
1595  // We don't want to have to hide both the block and it's BP class entry
1596  if (blueprint == null) continue;
1597 
1598  Debug.Assert(blueprintClass != null);
1599  if (blueprintClass == null) continue;
1600 
1601  blueprintClass.AddBlueprint(blueprint);
1602  }
1603  m_definitions.m_blueprintClassEntries.Clear();
1604 
1605  // Production block inventory constraints need to be initialized here, after the blueprint classes are finished
1606  foreach (var entry in m_definitions.m_definitionsById)
1607  {
1608  var definition = entry.Value as MyProductionBlockDefinition;

1637  private void AddEntriesToEnvironmentItemClasses()
1638  {
1639  foreach (var entry in m_definitions.m_environmentItemsEntries)
1640  {
1641  if (!entry.Enabled) continue;
1642 
1643  MyEnvironmentItemsDefinition itemsDefinition = null;
1644  MyEnvironmentItemDefinition itemDefinition = null;
1645 
1646  MyDefinitionId classId = new MyDefinitionId(MyObjectBuilderType.Parse(entry.Type), entry.Subtype);
1647  if (!TryGetDefinition<MyEnvironmentItemsDefinition>(classId, out itemsDefinition))
1648  {
1649  string errorString = "Environment items definition " + classId.ToString() + " not found!";
1650  MyDefinitionErrors.Add(MyModContext.BaseGame, errorString, TErrorSeverity.Warning);
1651  Debug.Assert(false, errorString);
1652  continue;
1653  }
1654 
1655  itemDefinition = FindEnvironmentItemByEntry(itemsDefinition, entry);
1656 
1657  // Item definition can be null if it is not public.
1658  // We don't want to have to hide both the item's definition and it's class entry
1659  if (itemDefinition == null) continue;
1660 
1661  var subtypeId = MyStringHash.GetOrCompute(entry.ItemSubtype);
1662  itemsDefinition.AddItemDefinition(subtypeId, entry.Frequency, false);
1663  }
1664 
1665  // Compute all frequencies at the end.
1666  foreach (var def in GetDefinitionsOfType<MyEnvironmentItemsDefinition>())
1667  {
1668  def.RecomputeFrequencies();
1669  }
1670 
1671  m_definitions.m_environmentItemsEntries.Clear();
1672  }

4205  private static void ProcessField(MyModContext context, object fieldOwnerInstance, FieldInfo field, bool includeMembers = true)
4206  {

4208  if (extensions.Length > 0 && field.FieldType == typeof(string))
4209  {
4210  string contentFile = (string)field.GetValue(fieldOwnerInstance);
4211  ProcessContentFilePath(context, ref contentFile, extensions, true);
4212  field.SetValue(fieldOwnerInstance, contentFile);

4214  else if (field.FieldType == typeof(string[]))

4216  string[] stringArray = (string[])field.GetValue(fieldOwnerInstance);
4217 
4218  if (stringArray != null)
4219  {
4220  for (int fileIndex = 0; fileIndex < stringArray.Length; ++fileIndex)
4221  ProcessContentFilePath(context, ref stringArray[fileIndex], extensions, false);
4222 
4223  field.SetValue(fieldOwnerInstance, stringArray);
4224  }
4225  }
4226  else if (includeMembers && (field.FieldType.IsClass || (field.FieldType.IsValueType && !field.FieldType.IsPrimitive)))
4227  {
4228  var instance = field.GetValue(fieldOwnerInstance);
4229  var enumerable = instance as System.Collections.IEnumerable;
4230  if (enumerable != null)
4231  {
4232  foreach (var x in enumerable)
4233  {
4234  var subfields = x.GetType().GetFields(BindingFlags.Public | BindingFlags.Instance);
4235  if (subfields.Length > 0)
4236  {
4237  foreach (FieldInfo subField in subfields)
4238  {
4239  ProcessField(context, x, subField, false); // Process only one level members
4240  }
4241  }
4242  }
4243  }
4244  else if (instance != null)

4246  ProcessSubfields(context, field, instance);
